333
00:33:37,415 --> 00:33:40,785
And the fumbling Feds.
  Where the hell
  did they come from?

334
00:33:40,818 --> 00:33:45,857
They couldn't find a puddle
 in the rain and they certainly
 couldn't find me,

335
00:33:45,890 --> 00:33:48,192
unless they knew exactly
   where to look.

336
00:33:50,161 --> 00:33:52,563
The whole assignment reeked,
   Neil.

337
00:33:52,597 --> 00:33:54,799
I don't know
 what happened, Della.

338
00:33:56,868 --> 00:33:59,170
You were the professional.

339
00:33:59,203 --> 00:34:01,439
You were the best.

340
00:34:01,472 --> 00:34:04,409
You got sloppy
  and you got caught.

341
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:07,578
You were supposed to fix
 the problem, not become one.

342
00:34:07,612 --> 00:34:10,181
What do you think this
   business is, huh?

343
00:34:10,214 --> 00:34:11,649
(CHUCKLES)

344
00:34:11,682 --> 00:34:15,486
We don't have a pension plan.
 We don't have profit sharing.

345
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:20,158
We don't have a killers ball
   every Christmas.

346
00:34:20,191 --> 00:34:23,561
And we don't have somebody
 to cover us when you screw up!

347
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:27,899
Hell, it's not a job at all.

348
00:34:27,932 --> 00:34:30,334
It's a way of life,
you know that.

349
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:33,838
As it is, we did get you out.

350
00:34:35,473 --> 00:34:36,874
All right, Neil.

351
00:34:38,376 --> 00:34:40,545
Here I am.

352
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:43,581
I'm out, you helped,
 and the deal was
 one last assignment.

353
00:34:43,614 --> 00:34:45,416
So, what is it?

354
00:34:45,450 --> 00:34:48,152
Good! Here's the file.

355
00:34:48,186 --> 00:34:50,621
You are really
going to love this one.

356
00:34:50,655 --> 00:34:53,157
It's right up your ally.

357
00:34:53,191 --> 00:34:57,395
Undercover.
   Professional marks, tough,
   well-trained competition,

358
00:34:57,428 --> 00:35:01,466
plenty of room to operate,
